      "slug": "alzheimers-smart-speaker",
      "name": "Alzheimers Smart Speaker",
      "description_short": "A research-driven smart speaker prototype using Python, voice AI, and a companion mobile app to support dementia and Alzheimer's patients with reminders, wellbeing checks, and SOS alerts.",
      "description_long": "The Alzheimer's Smart Speaker project was developed at Cardiff University as part of a research initiative exploring conversational AI for dementia support. As project lead, I developed both the hardware prototype and the cross-platform companion app.\n\nThe physical device, built using a Raspberry Pi, included motion sensors to trigger wellbeing check-ins, natural voice conversations, radio playback, news reading, and medication reminders. Custom Python scripts and Mycroft AI handled voice recognition, conversation flows, and automated behaviours.\n\nThe companion mobile app enables caregivers to configure medical information, schedule events, receive SOS alerts, and send direct messages to the smart speaker. Both systems communicate bi-directionally in real time using Firebase, enabling seamless integration between hardware and mobile.",
